# Architecture plan for Issue #125: Reduce right-side padding of the chat message area

## Module structure, file organization, shared types
- `frontend/src/styles.css` owns the Tailwind component-layer styles for the chat panel, message list, and combined feed spacing. This is the expected implementation surface.
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` renders the unified chat feed and message cards, but no markup, state, polling, history-loading, or accessibility changes are required.
- `shared/src/*`, `backend/src/*`, and database migrations remain out of scope because this is a CSS-only layout adjustment.

## Dependencies between issues
- Issue #125 has no direct implementation dependency and can be applied independently.
- It pairs with earlier left-padding work from Issue 5.12, so the new right-side values should keep the feed visually balanced with the already-reduced left padding.

## Key design decisions
- Reduce right-side wrapper spacing so message cards can use more horizontal width: `.tlhn-chat-panel` `pr-3` to `pr-1`, remove `.tlhn-chat-list` `pr-1`, and reduce `.tlhn-chat-list-combined` `pr-2` to `pr-1`.
- Keep `.tlhn-chat-message` itself at `p-0`; remaining horizontal whitespace is coming from wrappers rather than the message item.
- Preserve existing TLHN styling, borders, scroll behavior, message ordering, avatars, display names, and timestamps.
- Validate with the frontend build or lint/typecheck command after implementation.
